	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001460_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1'--> 
<!--Hand 01 31 top left--><!--Hand 02 67480 top right--><!--Hand 03 <p>D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. David Livingstone</p> top right-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>Kongone Harbour</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">31<hi rend="sup underline">st</hi> July 1859</p>
<lb/><p><persName>Mess<hi rend="sup underline">rs</hi> Pye, Brothers</persName></p>
<lb/><p>Sir</p>
<lb/><p>As you kindly 
<lb/>undertook the examination 
<lb/>of the <term type="plant">Buaze</term> which I 
<lb/>brought home in 1856 
<lb/>and reported favourably 
<lb/>there on though the specimen 
<lb/>was too small for 
<lb/>any manufacture, 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001460_0002"/><!--pb/@n='2'--> 
<lb/>I have taken the liberty 
<lb/>to transmit through the 
<lb/>Foreign Office a box 
<lb/>and two barrels of the 
<lb/>same fibre in the hope 
<lb/>that it may be 
<w>con-<lb break="no"/>venient</w> for you to 
<lb/>convert a portion of it 
<lb/>into cloth, or other 
<lb/>materials proper for 
<lb/>a thorough trial of its 
<lb/>properties. The seed 
<lb/>contains a valuable 
<lb/>oil for painting and 
<lb/>the plant itself grows 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001460_0003"/><!--pb/@n='3'--> 
<lb/>on soil unfit for other 
<lb/>cultivation and no pains 
<lb/>are required in rearing 
<lb/>the crop as it yields by 
<lb/>being pollarded. Seeds 
<lb/>have been sent to Natal 
<lb/>and India and should 
<lb/>you be able to produce 
<lb/>a fabric of finer and 
<lb/>stronger quality than flax, 
<lb/>there is but little doubt 
<lb/>but H. M. Secretary 
<lb/>of State for Foreign 
<lb/>Affairs would encourage 
<lb/>its production in our 
<lb/>own colonies</p>

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001460_0004"/><!--pb/@n='4'-->
<lb/><p>Your report on its strength 
<lb/>bleaching properties &amp;c 
<lb/>if addressed to the Foreign 
<lb/>Office would <choice><sic>recieve</sic><corr>receive</corr></choice>
<lb/>the attention it merited</p>
<lb/><p rend="right">Your Obedient Servant</p>
<lb/><p rend="right">David Livingstone</p>
			
</div>
